  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nMy Nethermind client didn't have TTD of `50000000000000000` configured when the ropsten testnet merged, so it did hang at block `12350712`. Setting TTD and restarting Nethermind didn't change anything, so I deleted `datadir/nethermind_db/ropsten/` and restarted Nethermind (with TTD of `50000000000000000`). (This right there is a bug on it's own. It should be possible to advance with the merge even if the required config option wasn't configured at the time the merge happened. It should not be required to delete the database and start from scratch.)\r\n\r\nNethermind did sync up until block `12350751` but doesn't finish syncing the ropsten testnet.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nStart nethermind with\r\n\r\n```\r\nNETHERMIND_CONFIG=\"ropsten\"\r\nNETHERMIND_JSONRPCCONFIG_ENABLED=\"true\"\r\nNETHERMIND_JSONRPCCONFIG_HOST=\"0.0.0.0\"\r\nNETHERMIND_INITCONFIG_LOGFILENAME=\"log.txt\"\r\nNETHERMIND_MERGECONFIG_TERMINALTOTALDIFFICULTY=\"50000000000000000\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nNethermind syncs to the ropsten latest block\r\n\r\n**What actually happens**\r\nNethermind stops at downloading block `12350751` over and over again: [nethermind-ropsten-log.txt](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/8877379/nethermind-ropsten-log.txt)\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS\r\n - Version: 1.13.2\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nRestarting nethermind didn't change anything",
